solution: Multiplying both sides by $4x-4$ and by 3 gives $3(3x-1) = 2(4x-4)$.  Expanding the products on both sides gives $9x-3 = 8x - 8$.  Subtracting $8x$ from both sides $x -3 = -8$ and adding 3 to both sides gives $x = \boxed{-5}$.
model_solution:
## Step 1: Multiply both sides of the equation by the denominator
$4x - 4 \cdot \frac{3x - 1}{4x - 4} = \frac23 \cdot (4x - 4)$
## Step 2: Simplify the equation
$(4x - 4) \cdot \frac{3x - 1}{4x - 4} = \frac23 \cdot (4x - 4) \Rightarrow 3x - 1 = \frac23 \cdot (4x - 4)$
## Step 3: Distribute $\frac23$ on the right side of the equation
$3x - 1 = \frac23 \cdot 4x - \frac23 \cdot 4$
## Step 4: Simplify both sides of the equation
$3x - 1 = \frac23 \cdot 4x - \frac23 \cdot 4 \Rightarrow 3x - 1 = \frac{8x - 8}{3}$
## Step 5: Multiply both sides of the equation by 3 to eliminate the fraction
$9x - 3 = 8x - 8$
## Step 6: Subtract 8x from both sides of the equation
$x - 3 = -8$
## Step 7: Add 3 to both sides of the equation
$x = -8 + 3$
## Step 8: Simplify the right side of the equation
$x = -5$
## Step 9:  $x = -5$
## Step 10: Check the solution to ensure it is valid
Check if $x = -5$ satisfies the original equation $\frac{3x - 1}{4x-4} = \frac23$.
